<br>
- Axes, Hammers and Swords are all based on STR. No DEX involved here.<br>
<br>
- Axes and Swords are slash damage, Hammer is crush damage.<br>
The natural resistances of armor types against each type of damage is as follow :<br>
Cloth is Neutral to all types of weapons.<br>
The first adjective is resistance to thrust (irrelevant here, but for comparison), second is resistance to crush, third is resistance to slash.<br>
Exemple, Plare armor is resistant to thrust, vulnerable to crush, and neutral to slash.<br>
<br>
Class Armor Thrust Crush Slash <br>
Albion :<br>
Plate Resistant Vulnerable Neutral <br>
Chain Vulnerable Resistant Neutral <br>
Studded Vulnerable Resistant Neutral <br>
Leather Resistant Vulnerable Neutral <br>
<br>
Hibernian armor resist table <br>
Scale Neutral Resistant Vulnerable <br>
Reinforced Neutral Vulnerable Resistant <br>
Leather Neutral Vulnerable Resistant <br>
<br>
Basically : Slash will either be neutral (Albion) or have a bonus (Hibernia) against the &quot;heavier&quot; armor types, and will either be neutral (alb) or penalized (hib) against the &quot;softer&quot; armor types.<br>
With the exception of plate, it's the opposite for crush.<br>
<br>
So, many midgard melee classes prefer slash over crush, because the penalties against hibernia soft armors are somewhat mitigated by the lower absorption of those types of armor. On the other hand, adding a penalty against already tough opponents can be difficult for a crush user.<br>
<br>
- The third factor is styles. Hammer and Axe styles are generally favored above sword styles (though it is somewhat mitigated if end regen is available).<br>
<br>
Axes have notably good front and rear positional styles, that are relatively &quot;easy&quot; to use in RvR for good damage.<br>
However, sword has an interesting anytime style (polar rift), which is not a good style in itself because of its prohibitive endurance cost, but can be a tremedous boon (easily spammable with lag or during confusing melees) when endurance regen is available, so sword is also a good choice nowadays (though the dueling or &quot;gank group&quot; skald who often fight 1vs1 would still prefer axe because of the positional and reactive styles).<br>
<br>
Hope this help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ookash>Ookash</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/2/03 6:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=535.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapons</span><hr size=1> So my reason for doing the hammer troll is uncomplicated and has no detailed math as to why I choose hammer.  I did not compare the value of style vs style.  At no point did it occur to me as to how to UBERIZE my troll skald.  <br>
