<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://home.nc.rr.com/obsidianguard/wyrd/Midgard.htm">home.nc.rr.com/obsidiangu...idgard.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Notice that the top 3 AXE styles are positional based, where sword and hammer have only one positional style in the top three styles.  Since parry never happens in RvR the parry styles are negated for everyone.  Warriors can use the block-react styles to good effect, Skald's can't.  Thus for a Skald you want to plan your weapon spec to make use of anytime or positional based styles.  <br>
<br>
I use Sword, but I'm in a regualr group with an Aug Sammy so I have endless endurance.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seductroo>seductroo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/9/03 4:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=535.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jadedsouls.com/art/sig1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Styles</span><hr size=1> Kilg,<br>
